	(48,1,'2015-05-19 14:28:03','2015-05-19 18:28:03','Wiki Ed partners with academic associations and universities to encourage more instructors to assign students to edit Wikipedia as part of their coursework.\n\nIn our academic association partnerships, the association formally encourages its members to participate in Wiki Ed\'s program. Wiki Ed staff support the instructors from that discipline in crafting an assignment that will enable students to fill content gaps on Wikipedia in that field.\n\nIn our university partnerships, a campus department such as a library, teaching and learning center, or writing center formally partners with Wiki Ed. We provide training for the staff of that campus department on best practices for using Wikipedia as a teaching tool in university classrooms, and they do outreach on campus to get more instructors on that campus to participate in the program. Wiki Ed staff provides support for the participants as they engage with editing Wikipedia.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3>Active Wiki Ed Partners</h3>\n<a href=\"http://www.psychologicalscience.org/index.php/members/aps-wikipedia-initiative\">Association for Psychological Science</a>\n<a>Communication across the Curriculum at Louisiana State University</a>\n<a href=\"http://www.mpsanet.org/Membership/WikipediaInitiative/tabid/948/Default.aspx#.VSWZOxPF868\">Midwest Political Science Association</a>\n<a href=\"http://www.nwsa.org/wikiedu\">National Women\'s Studies Association</a>\n\n&nbsp;\n<h3>Become a partner</h3>\nWe are actively seeking additional associations and universities who are interested in partnering with us. Reach out to Jami Mathewson, Educational Partnerships Manager, at <a href=\"mailto:jami@wikiedu.org\">jami@wikiedu.org</a> for more details','Partnerships','','inherit','open','open','','9-autosave-v1','','','2015-05-19 14:28:03','2015-05-19 18:28:03','',9,'http://wikiedu.dev/2015/05/19/9-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
