	(125,1,'2015-05-22 13:42:07','2015-05-22 17:42:07','<div class=\"toc-block\"><h3>Table of Contents</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>1. <a href=\"#\">Subject-specific handouts</a></li>\r\n<li>2. <a href=\"#\">Classroom handouts</a></li>\r\n<li>3. <a href=\"#\">Selecting article topics</a></li>\r\n<li>4. <a href=\"#\">Course pages</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n    \r\n  \r\n        <ul>\r\n          <li>5. <a href=\"#basics\">Learn the basics</a></li>\r\n          <li>6. <a href=\"#\">Assignment planning</a></li>\r\n          <li>7. <a href=\"#\">Motivating students</a></li>\r\n          <li>8. <a href=\"#\">Teaching tools</a></li>\r\n        </ul>\r\n     \r\n    </div>\r\nOver nine terms of running the Wikipedia Education Program in the United States and Canada, we’ve helped more than 300 instructors in higher education implement a Wikipedia assignment. Through their experiences and feedback, we’ve put together some assignment design guidelines and online training for instructors and students.\r\n\r\nIf you’re interested in using Wikipedia as a teaching tool in your classroom, here’s the information you need to know. Have questions not answered here? Reach out to us at contact(at)wikiedu.org.\r\n<div class=\"tools\">\r\n<a href=\"#basics\" id=\"basics\"></a>\r\n<h3>Learn the basics</h3>\r\nThe instructor training and the instructor basics brochure will walk you through the editing basics and community norms on Wikipedia, information instructors find crucial for designing assignments that set students up for success.\r\n<ul class=\"tools-list\">\r\n	<li>Training for educators<button class=\"btn btn-default\">Start Training</button></li>\r\n	<li>Instructor Basics: how to use Wikipedia as a teaching tool<button class=\"btn btn-default\">Download</button></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<div class=\"tools\">\r\n<a href=\"#planning\" id=\"planning\"></a>\r\n<h3>Assignment Planning</h3>\r\nIf you haven’t spoken to a Wikipedia Education Program representative about your assignment plan yet, the next two resources will be helpful.\r\nOur Case Studies collection highlights various models and learning objectives for incorporating Wikipedia into a course. The Syllabus collection provides detailed information on how instructors have run successful assignments. In particular, the model 12-week syllabus represents our best recommendations for running a full-term Wikipedia research and writing assignment.\r\n<ul class=\"tools-list\">\r\n	<li>Case Studies: How Instructors are teaching with Wikipedia<button class=\"btn btn-default\">Download</button></li>\r\n	<li>The Syllabus: A 12-week assignment to write a Wikipedia article<button class=\"btn btn-default\">Download</button></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>','For Instructors','','inherit','open','open','','4-revision-v1','','','2015-05-22 13:42:07','2015-05-22 17:42:07','',4,'http://wikiedu.dev.192.168.1.74.xip.io/2015/05/22/4-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
	(126,1,'2015-05-22 18:08:15','2015-05-22 22:08:15','[toc levels=3 title=\"Table of contents\"] \r\nThe Wiki Education Foundation serves as the bridge between academia and Wikipedia. A small 501(c)3 nonprofit, we run programs that seek to build connections between universities and Wikipedia and other Wikimedia projects in the United States and Canada.\r\n\r\nIn our most established program, Wiki Ed supports the Wikipedia Education Program in the United States and Canada. Since 2010, university instructors participating in the program have assigned their students to add content to course-related articles on Wikipedia. Students gain key 21st century skills like media literacy, writing and research development, and critical thinking, while content gaps on Wikipedia get filled thanks to students’ efforts.\r\n\r\nFormed in 2013, Wiki Ed is a spin-off of the Wikimedia Foundation, the nonprofit organization that runs Wikipedia.\r\n\r\n<h3>Our Staff</h3>[team_manager category=\'staff\' orderby=\'menu_order\' limit=\'0\' exclude=\'\' post__in=\'\' layout=\'staff\' image_layout=\'circle\' image_size=\'post-thumbnail\']\r\n<h3>Our Board</h3>[team_manager category=\'board\' orderby=\'menu_order\' limit=\'0\' post__in=\'\' exclude=\'\' layout=\'board\' image_layout=\'circle\' image_size=\'thumbnail\']\r\n\r\n','About Us','','inherit','open','open','','11-revision-v1','','','2015-05-22 18:08:15','2015-05-22 22:08:15','',11,'http://wikiedu.dev.192.168.1.74.xip.io/2015/05/22/11-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),
